for the GK Game Center
view controller,

00:04:06.306 --> 00:04:07.596 A:middle
setting up the delegate to cells

00:04:07.596 --> 00:04:09.186 A:middle
so that you can dismiss
it appropriately,

00:04:10.156 --> 00:04:11.176 A:middle
set up your view state

00:04:11.176 --> 00:04:14.226 A:middle
to whatever appropriate initial
view state you wish to show.

00:04:15.266 --> 00:04:16.516 A:middle
And here's a little
bit of a wrinkle,

00:04:16.516 --> 00:04:18.036 A:middle
the throttle rendering call.

00:04:18.036 --> 00:04:19.586 A:middle
We'll get into that
in just a moment.

00:04:19.646 --> 00:04:21.755 A:middle
And then, finally, you're going

00:04:21.755 --> 00:04:23.816 A:middle
to present the view
controller just like you would

00:04:23.816 --> 00:04:25.856 A:middle
with any other UI view
controller within you game.

00:04:25.856 --> 00:04:29.196 A:middle
Now that throttle rendering call
that I'm talking about, right?

00:04:30.056 --> 00:04:32.886 A:middle
As I mentioned, the GK
Game Center view controller

00:04:32.886 --> 00:04:35.516 A:middle
with iOS 7 is partially
transparent.

00:04:36.556 --> 00:04:38.266 A:middle
Moreover, it's also
doing some blurring

00:04:38.266 --> 00:04:40.406 A:middle
and other heavy compositing
on the GPU.

00:04:40.886 --> 00:04:44.036 A:middle
So in order to make this
present as smoothly as possible

00:04:44.036 --> 00:04:46.346 A:middle
so that players can get in
and out of the menu and back

00:04:46.346 --> 00:04:48.706 A:middle
to playing your game,
you don't really need

00:04:48.706 --> 00:04:52.056 A:middle
to be running graphics at 60
frames per second and you're

00:04:52.056 --> 00:04:53.766 A:middle
about to push this
view controller over.

00:04:54.246 --> 00:04:56.906 A:middle
So you can step back in
the gas pedal a little bit

00:04:56.906 --> 00:04:58.646 A:middle
and let the view
controller present,

00:04:59.106 --> 00:05:02.476 A:middle
dismiss when you need to,
and get right back to it.

