So really, that's
all that's changed

00:05:04.406 --> 00:05:05.996 A:middle
with the GK Game
Center view controller.

00:05:06.336 --> 00:05:11.166 A:middle
It's really just the exact
same API with a brand new look

00:05:11.166 --> 00:05:13.546 A:middle
that we feel really makes it

00:05:13.596 --> 00:05:15.196 A:middle
that much more ingrained
within your game.

00:05:16.546 --> 00:05:19.716 A:middle
So let's move on to the
next new topic of today.

00:05:20.496 --> 00:05:21.636 A:middle
Leaderboard Sets.

00:05:22.526 --> 00:05:24.176 A:middle
This is something we're
very excited about.

00:05:25.156 --> 00:05:29.116 A:middle
Today, on-- in iOS 6 device
or on OS X Mountain Lion,

00:05:29.576 --> 00:05:32.286 A:middle
your game currently has
at most 25 leaderboards

00:05:32.286 --> 00:05:34.426 A:middle
that it can define and
use on Game Center.

00:05:35.756 --> 00:05:37.026 A:middle
Now, I'm happy to tell you

00:05:37.576 --> 00:05:40.406 A:middle
that we have increased
this maximum limit

00:05:40.406 --> 00:05:42.156 A:middle
to 100 leaderboards.

00:05:42.556 --> 00:05:45.436 A:middle
You can have at most 100
leaderboards in a flat list

00:05:45.856 --> 00:05:47.506 A:middle
that your game can
use in Game Center.

00:05:48.306 --> 00:05:49.506 A:middle
And we're not stopping there.

00:05:50.326 --> 00:05:52.876 A:middle
With this new feature that
we have, Leaderboard Sets,

00:05:53.126 --> 00:05:55.776 A:middle
we're increasing actually
the maximum amount

00:05:55.776 --> 00:05:58.426 A:middle
of leaderboards you can use
within your game twentyfold

00:05:58.776 --> 00:06:00.536 A:middle
to 500 maximum leaderboards.

WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:05:58.776 --> 00:06:00.536 A:middle
to 500 maximum leaderboards.

00:06:01.406 --> 00:06:03.346 A:middle
And now, with Leaderboard Sets,

00:06:03.346 --> 00:06:05.736 A:middle
we're introducing an
organizational hierarchy,

00:06:05.736 --> 00:06:08.046 A:middle
a structure that you can
impose on these leaderboards.

00:06:08.626 --> 00:06:11.266 A:middle
You can think of Leaderboard
Sets as a tagging architecture

00:06:11.266 --> 00:06:14.226 A:middle
where a single leaderboard can
belong to many different sets,

00:06:14.826 --> 00:06:17.406 A:middle
and likewise, a single
set can contain many

00:06:17.406 --> 00:06:18.456 A:middle
different leaderboards.

00:06:19.256 --> 00:06:21.646 A:middle
Then you have at most
100 sets that you can use

00:06:21.646 --> 00:06:24.126 A:middle
within your game and at
most 100 leaderboards

00:06:24.126 --> 00:06:26.186 A:middle
that you can put
in a single set.

00:06:26.816 --> 00:06:29.016 A:middle
So why are we asking you

00:06:29.016 --> 00:06:32.396 A:middle
to use Leaderboard Sets before
you can actually unlock the full

00:06:32.396 --> 00:06:34.616 A:middle
500 leaderboards for
use within your game?

00:06:34.896 --> 00:06:37.526 A:middle
It actually comes down
to usability issue.

00:06:38.466 --> 00:06:41.006 A:middle
Let's say you've got a Water
Planet group of stages, right?

00:06:41.426 --> 00:06:43.336 A:middle
And also, for this
group of stages,

00:06:43.336 --> 00:06:44.796 A:middle
you have a boss level
at the end.

00:06:45.136 --> 00:06:47.936 A:middle
And maybe you've also
got different levels

00:06:47.936 --> 00:06:49.586 A:middle
of difficulty-- easy,
medium, hard.

00:06:49.586 --> 00:06:52.036 A:middle
So one possible leaderboard

00:06:52.036 --> 00:06:54.296 A:middle
that your game has is the
Water Planet Boss Level

00:06:54.296 --> 00:06:55.236 A:middle
Medium leaderboard.

00:06:56.176 --> 00:06:58.926 A:middle
You, being the endeavoring game
developer that you are, however,

00:06:58.926 --> 00:07:02.106 A:middle
also have 499 other leaderboards

WEBVTT
